{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ground|type2=Ghost}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Golurk}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ground|prevnum=622|prev=Golett|nextnum=624|next=Pawniard|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Golurk\n|jname=ゴルーグ\n|jtranslit=Gorūgu\n|tmname=Goloog\n|category=Automaton\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Ground\n|type2=Ghost\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Iron Fist\n|ability2=Klutz\n|abilityd=No Guard\n|ndex=623\n|udex=129\n|u2dex=272\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=092\n|height-ftin=9\'02"\n|height-m=2.8\n|weight-lbs=727.5\n|weight-kg=330.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Mineral\n|eggcycles=25\n|expyield=169\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|gendercode=255\n|color=Green\n|catchrate=90\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=golurk\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Golurk\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ゴルーグ\'\'\' \'\'Goloog\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Ground|Ghost}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Golett}} starting at [[level]] 43.\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Juanita Golurk {{#switch: {{#expr: {{#time: H}} mod 2}}|0=Black|1=White}} Fly.png|thumb|left|250px|{{#switch: {{#expr: {{#time: H}} mod 2}}|0=Golurk|1={{Shiny}} Golurk}} flying]]\nGolurk is a bipedal automaton Pokémon resembling a suit of armor. It said to have been invented by ancient people to serve as a laborer. It is mainly teal in color with yellow swirls on its shoulders and hands. It has a small head compared to its body, and pale yellow eyes, one of which turns to its left at the bottom, unlike {{p|Golett}}\'s eye, which turns right. There is a crack across the chest of the armor, which is patched diagonally with a brown seal resembling a belt. It has a crystal-like formation on each shoulder, and there are large bangles on its wrists and ankles. It has a Roman armor-like "skirt" and flat feet beneath.\n\nDespite its large size, Golurk is capable of flying by retracting its hands into its arms and its legs and feet into its body, then taking off like a rocket. If the seal on its chest is removed, its energy runs wild. This causes it to rage and fly around uncontrollably without being able to land itself. It is also capable of forming a cannon by pulling its legs into its body and standing on its hands, as seen in [[PokéPark 2: Wonders Beyond]]. Golurk was created by an ancient civilization to protect people and Pokémon.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Hapu Golurk.png|thumb|left|250px|Golurk in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:Juanita Golurk Black.png|thumb|left|250px|A {{Shiny}} Golurk in the anime]]\n\n====Major appearances====\nA Golurk appeared in [[M14|\'\'White—Victini and Zekrom\'\' and \'\'Black—Victini and Reshiram\'\']], under the ownership of [[Juanita]]. It acts as her assistant and partner at her souvenir shop. It is also {{Shiny}} in the latter movie.\n\nA Golurk appeared in \'\'[[BW082|An Epic Defense Force!]]\'\' as an {{a|illusion}} in a movie directed by [[Luke]].\n\nA Golurk appeared in \'\'[[BW096|Meloetta and the Undersea Temple!]]\'\' and \'\'[[BW097|Unova\'s Survival Crisis!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Ridley]]. He used Golurk to fly with him, and it was also used to defend {{an|Meloetta}} from {{TRT}}. It was also used to battle two {{tc|Team Rocket Grunt}}s\' {{p|Golem}} and {{p|Rhydon}}. After that, it battled against the members of the [[Forces of Nature]] in their {{DL|List of Pokémon with form differences|Forces of Nature|Therian Formes}}.\n\nMultiple Golurk appeared in \'\'[[BW120|Ash and N: A Clash of Ideals!]]\'\', \'\'[[BW121|Team Plasma and the Awakening Ceremony!]]\'\', and \'\'[[BW122|What Lies Beyond Truth and Ideals!]]\'\'. They were owned by [[Cedric Juniper\'s assistants]] and used at the {{an|White Ruins}}, but they were later turned against their owners by [[Colress]]. They were eventually freed when {{AP|Pikachu}} and {{DL|Recurring wild Pokémon in the anime|Reshiram}} destroyed Colress\'s mind-control device.\n\nA Golurk appeared in \'\'[[BW134|The Journalist from Another Region!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Rodney]]. It was used during the [[Pokémon Sumo Tournament]]. Golurk made it through to the final round and faced off against {{Ash}} and {{AP|Pignite}}, but it ended up losing against them.\n\nA Golurk appeared in \'\'[[SM104|That\'s Some Spicy Island Research!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Hapu]]. Golurk was first seen assisting Hapu in a Poni Island radish field. It attacked Ash when Hapu believed he was the one who had been stealing radishes from the field, and defeated {{AP|Pikachu}} in battle. Golurk has since made further appearances in the {{series|Sun & Moon}}. Hapu commonly uses Golurk to fly around [[Poni Island]].\n\n====Minor appearances====\nGolurk debuted in \'\'[[BW038|Movie Time! Zorua in "The Legend of the Pokémon Knight"!]]\'\'. It appeared as an actor in a movie based around the [[Wonder Launcher]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW096|Golurk|Ash\'s Pokédex|Golurk, the Automaton Pokémon and the evolved form of {{p|Golett}}. {{m|Fly}}ing faster than the speed of sound, Golurk loses control when the seal on its chest is removed.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n{{Animedexheader|Alola}}\n{{Animedexbody|SM104|Golurk|Rotom Pokédex|Golurk, the Automaton Pokémon. A {{t|Ground}} and {{t|Ghost}} type. When the seal on its chest is removed, it loses control of its own energy.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Sun & Moon\'\'|Alola}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:AZ Golurk PG.png|thumb|250px|Golurk in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\n[[AZ]]\'s Golurk appeared in \'\'[[PG18|The Redemption]]\'\'. It battled {{ga|Calem}} and his {{p|Chesnaught}}, and lost. Another Golurk was seen under the ownership of a soldier, during a fantasy of a story from the past, where it was one of the many Pokémon fighting in the great war of [[Kalos]] 3,000 years previously.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Shauntal Golurk Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Golurk in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n[[Shauntal]] has a Golurk which first appeared in \'\'[[PS511|Dream a Little Dream]]\'\'.\n\nA Golurk appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PAXY25|Flabébé Blooms]]\'\'.\n\n[[AZ]]\'s Golurk appeared in \'\'[[PAXY39|Epilogue]]\'\'.\n\n[[Hapu]] owns a Golurk, which first appeared in [[PASM23]].\n\n===In the Victini and the Black Hero: Zekrom manga===\n[[Juanita]]\'s Golurk appears in {{ma|White—Victini and Zekrom|the manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M14|White—Victini and Zekrom]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon RéBURST manga===\nA Golurk appears as the [[Burst]] form of Battsu.\n\nIn [[RB73]], [[Fraud]] uses a Golurk Burst as one of his forms after receiving the power of Arcades.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Golurk (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===\'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'===\nThree Golurk appeared in \'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'.\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=ground|type2=ghost}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=129|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=272|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=Golurk were created to protect people and Pokémon. They run on a mysterious energy.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=092|label1=Coastal|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It is said that Golurk were ordered to protect people and Pokémon by the ancient people who made them.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.}}\n{{