ata===\n{{Spindata/Head|type=Ground|type2=Ghost}}\n{{Spindata/RumbleBlast|col=6|type=Ground\n|att=4\n|def=3\n|speed=3\n}}\n|-\n{{Spindata/PokéPark2|col=6|type=Ground|ndex=623\n|strong=[[File:Oshawott icon.png|link=Oshawott (Pokémon)]][[File:Snivy icon.png|link=Snivy (Pokémon)]]\n|weak=[[File:Pikachu icon.png|link=Pikachu (Pokémon)]]\n|pad=He was watching the entrance of the warehouse. He is powerful and acts without thinking, but he means no harm.\n}}\n|-\n{{Spindata/Battle Trozei|col=3|type=Ground|ndex=623\n|power=2\n}}\n{{Spindata/Shuffle|col=3|type=Ground|ndex=623|num=451\n|min=60\n|max=105\n|raisemaxlevel=5\n|skill=Block Smash+\n|skilldesc=Sometimes clears three unbreakable-block disruptions.\n}}\n|-\n{{Spindata/GO|col=6|type=Ground|ndex=623\n|hatch=N/A\n|buddy=5\n|evolution=N/A\n|stamina=205\n|attack=222\n|defense=154\n|fast={{m|Astonish}}, {{m|Mud-Slap}}\n|special={{m|Shadow Punch}}, {{m|Dynamic Punch}}, {{m|Earth Power}}\n}}\n|}\n\n===Evolution===\n{{evobox-2\n|type1=Ground\n|type2=Ghost\n|no1=622\n|name1=Golett\n|type1-1=Ground\n|type2-1=Ghost\n|evo1={{bag|Rare Candy}}<br>{{color2|000|Level|Level 43}}\n|no2=623\n|name2=Golurk\n|type1-2=Ground\n|type2-2=Ghost}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=ground|type2=ghost}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=623}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=623}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=623}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|623|Golurk}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* According to Game Freak, Golurk and its pre-evolved form were both created by [[James Turner]].<ref>http://web.archive.org/web/20130115083652/http://www.gamefreak.co.jp/blog/staff/?p=204</ref>\n* [[PokéPark 2: Wonders Beyond]]\'s PokéPad entry refers to Golurk as a male, despite Golurk being genderless.\n* While Golurk has a 5% chance of holding the [[Light Clay]], it cannot learn {{m|Light Screen}} or {{m|Reflect}}.\n\n===Origin===\nGolurk and its pre-evolved form both appear to be based on {{wp|golem}}s and, considering its body structure and ability to learn {{m|Fly}}, {{wp|Mecha anime and manga#Super robot|giant robots}}. The crack and strap on its chest may be a reference to the golem in the Hebrew story \'\'{{wp|Golem#The classic narrative: The Golem of Prague|The Golem of Prague}}\'\'. The golem in this story was also believed to be able to summon the spirits of the dead, which was likely the reasoning for Golurk\'s Ghost-typing.\n\n====Name origin====\nGolurk is a combination of \'\'golem\'\' and \'\'lurk\'\' (referring to its {{t|Ghost}} type).\n\nGoloog is a combination of \'\'golem\'\' and サイボーグ \'\'saibōgu\'\' (cyborg).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=ground|type2=ghost\n|ja=ゴルーグ \'\'Goloog\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|ゴーレム \'\'gōremu\'\'|golem}} and {{tt|サイボーグ \'\'saibōgu\'\'|cyborg}}\n|fr=Golemastoc|frmeaning=From \'\'golem\'\' and \'\'{{tt|mastoc|massive}}\'\'\n|es=Golurk|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Golgantes|demeaning=From \'\'Golem\'\' and \'\'{{tt|gigante|Italian for \'giant\'}}\'\'\n|it=Golurk|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=골루그 \'\'Goloog\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=泥偶巨人 \'\'Ní\'ǒujùrén\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|泥人 \'\'nírén\'\'|clay figurine}}, {{tt|偶人 \'\'ǒurén\'\'|idol}}, and {{tt|巨人 \'\'jùrén\'\'|giant}}\n|ru=Голарк \'\'Golark\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ground|type2=Ghost}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ground|prevnum=622|prev=Golett|nextnum=624|next=Pawniard}}\n|}\n{{-}}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Artificial Pokémon]]\n\n[[de:Golgantes]]\n[[es:Golurk]]\n[[fr:Golemastoc]]\n[[it:Golurk]]\n[[ja:ゴルーグ]]\n[[zh:泥偶巨人]]'}